Here's how to implement all three requirements:

## 1. Intercept Back Navigation with a Confirmation Dialog

Override `OnBackButtonPressed` in your page:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (!_hasUnsavedChanges)
            return base.OnBackButtonPressed();

        // Fire-and-forget the async prompt; return true to cancel navigation immediately
        Dispatcher.Dispatch(async () =>
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (leave)
            {
                _hasUnsavedChanges = false;
                await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
            }
        });

        return true; // cancel the default back navigation
    }
}
```

> **Key detail:** `OnBackButtonPressed` is synchronous and must return `true` (cancel) immediately, so the async dialog is dispatched separately.

## 2. Custom "Cancel" Back Button

Replace Shell's default back button with a toolbar item:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{StaticResource CancelBackButton}">

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <BackButtonBehavior x:Key="CancelBackButton"
                            IsVisible="True"
                            TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </ContentPage.Resources>

    <!-- Or inline: -->
    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

Then in your view model or code-behind:

```csharp
public ICommand CancelCommand { get; }

public EditProductPage()
{
    InitializeComponent();

    CancelCommand = new Command(async () =>
    {
        if (!_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
            return;
        }

        bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard changes?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (leave)
        {
            _hasUnsavedChanges = false;
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
        }
    });
}
```

## What each piece covers

| Scenario | Handled by |
|---|---|
| Android hardware/gesture back | `OnBackButtonPressed` |
| Shell toolbar back button | `BackButtonBehavior.Command` |
| Custom button text | `BackButtonBehavior.TextOverride` |

**Note:** `OnBackButtonPressed` only fires for the Android hardware/swipe-back gesture. The `BackButtonBehavior.Command` intercepts the Shell navigation bar button. You need **both** to fully guard against unsaved-change loss.
